  "prompt": "My iPhone screen broke I have iCloud, would notifications I received transfer over to a replacement or would contacts transfer and notifications gone?",
  "response": "Let's break this down:\n\n*   **Contacts:** Yes, your contacts will transfer over. If you're using iCloud Contacts (which is the default and recommended), your contacts are stored in the cloud and will sync to your new iPhone once you sign in with your Apple ID and enable Contacts in iCloud settings.\n\n*   **Notifications:** No, historical notifications will **not** transfer to your new iPhone. Notifications are not stored in iCloud or backed up in a way that allows them to be restored to a new device. You will start fresh with notifications on your new phone.\n\nIn summary, expect your contacts to be safely restored via iCloud, but notifications will be reset on your replacement iPhone.",
